Transform the Minhaajulhudaa multi-platform hub from a prototype with sample data and basic structure into a fully functional, production-ready system. The plan addresses 80+ missing features across all four platforms (School, Masjid, Charity, Travels) including advanced LMS with video lessons/quizzes/assignments, exam system, comprehensive payment integration (Paystack/Stripe/Flutterwave), 24/7 Quran player with Archive.org audio integration, donation tracking with recurring payments, booking engine with dynamic pricing, shared CMS/blog/shop/LMS modules, authentication system, media management with Cloudinary, email notifications, and full admin CRUD interfaces ensuring everything works with GitHub DB.
Build comprehensive environment configuration system: Create .env.example with detailed documentation for GitHub DB (VITE_GITHUB_USER, VITE_GITHUB_REPO, VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN), payment gateways (Paystack, Stripe, Flutterwave with public/secret keys for each), Cloudinary for media (cloud name, API key/secret, upload preset), email service (SMTP endpoint, from address, API key), Archive.org API integration, and platform-specific settings. Update vite.config.ts to properly load environment variables and add runtime validation in src/lib/config.ts to ensure all required environment variables are present on startup.
Implement centralized authentication and authorization system: Create src/lib/auth directory with auth-context.tsx providing login/logout/register functionality using GitHub DB users collection, session management with localStorage/sessionStorage, role-based access control supporting roles (admin, teacher, student, donor, customer, volunteer), useAuth hook for accessing current user/permissions, and ProtectedRoute component. Implement password hashing with bcrypt-like client-side library, email verification workflow storing OTP in GitHub DB, and JWT-like token generation for secure session management. Add login/register pages for each platform (src/pages/school/auth, src/pages/masjid/auth, etc.) with proper form validation using react-hook-form and zod.
Build comprehensive payment integration system: Create src/lib/payment directory with unified payment service (payment-service.ts) that supports multiple providers (Paystack, Stripe, Flutterwave) with provider-specific implementations (paystack.ts, stripe.ts, flutterwave.ts). Implement payment initiation, transaction verification, webhook handlers, refund processing, and payment status tracking. Create reusable PaymentModal component (src/components/shared/PaymentModal.tsx) with amount input, provider selection, and redirect/popup handling. Add payment tracking to GitHub DB with transactions collection storing transactionId, userId, amount, currency, provider, status, metadata. Integrate payment system into School (tuition/shop/fees), Masjid (donations), Charity (campaigns), and Travels (package bookings) with proper success/failure handling and receipt generation.
Develop Cloudinary media management system: Create src/lib/cloudinary directory with upload service supporting images/videos/audio/documents, providing upload progress tracking, file optimization with automatic format conversion, folder organization by platform and content type, signed upload URLs for secure uploads, and media gallery component. Build MediaManager component (src/components/shared/MediaManager.tsx) with drag-and-drop upload, preview, search/filter, bulk operations, and media selection for content creation. Integrate media management into all admin forms (blog posts, products, campaigns, packages) and update GitHub DB schemas to store Cloudinary URLs with proper metadata (public_id, format, width, height, size).
Implement School Platform LMS (Learning Management System): Create complete LMS infrastructure at src/pages/school/lms with StudentPortal (dashboard, my-courses, course-viewer, assignments, grades, progress), TeacherPortal (course-management, assignment-grading, student-tracking, analytics), and AdminLMS (course-creation, enrollment-management, reports). Build course content viewer supporting video lessons with progress tracking (using HTML5 video with event listeners), PDF documents with page tracking, interactive quizzes with immediate feedback, timed assignments with auto-submission, discussion forums per course, and certificates upon completion. Create GitHub DB collections: lms_courses, lms_lessons, lms_assignments, lms_submissions, lms_grades, lms_enrollments, lms_progress. Implement rich course creation interface in admin with drag-drop lesson ordering, content upload to Cloudinary, quiz builder with multiple question types (multiple choice, true/false, short answer, essay), and grading rubrics.
Build comprehensive Online Exam System for School: Create src/pages/school/exams directory with exam infrastructure including ExamList (for students), ExamCreator (for teachers/admins), ExamTaker (exam interface with timer, question navigation, auto-save), ExamResults (detailed results with analytics), and ExamGrading (for teachers to grade subjective questions). Implement exam types (practice, assessment, final), question banks with categorization/tagging, randomized question selection, time limits with countdown timer, anti-cheating measures (fullscreen mode, tab switching detection, time tracking per question), automatic grading for objective questions, manual grading interface for subjective answers, detailed analytics (question-level statistics, student performance comparison), and grade export functionality. Store in GitHub DB collections: exams, exam_questions, exam_attempts, exam_answers, exam_results with proper relationships between collections.
Develop School Wiki/Knowledgebase system: Create src/pages/school/wiki with wiki infrastructure including WikiHome (category overview, search, recent changes), WikiArticle (article viewer with table of contents, related articles, edit history), WikiEditor (rich markdown editor with preview, image upload, formatting tools), and WikiCategory management. Implement features: markdown support with syntax highlighting, hierarchical category structure, full-text search across articles, revision history with diff viewer, article templates for consistency, cross-referencing between articles, favorite/bookmark system, and print-friendly views. Add admin interface for managing wiki structure, approving edits, and managing contributors. Store in GitHub DB: wiki_articles, wiki_categories, wiki_revisions, wiki_comments with full version control.
